consoleData.description: The percentage of overlapping attempts in the attempt window below which input automation detection is triggered at the success threshold.

uiData.label: sv_auto_cstrafe_lower_overlap_pct_threshold
uiData.helperText: The percentage of overlapping attempts in the attempt window below which input automation detection is triggered at the success threshold.

consoleData.description: The minimum number of counter-strafe attempts required for input automation detection. The player must be moving more than 135.2 units/s for their counter-strafe to be considered an attempt. An attempt is either considered a success (counter-strafing took place within a single tick), an overlap (both directions were held for 1+ ticks) or an underlap (neither direction was held for 1+ ticks).

uiData.label: sv_auto_cstrafe_min_attempts
uiData.helperText: The minimum number of counter-strafe attempts required for input automation detection. The player must be moving more than 135.2 units/s for their counter-strafe to be considered an attempt. An attempt is either considered a success (counter-strafing took place within a single tick), an overlap (both directions were held for 1+ ticks) or an underlap (neither direction was held for 1+ ticks).

consoleData.description: The length of sequential counter-strafe attempts evaluated relative to the success threshold. Input automation detection considers the best sequence within the larger attempt window.

uiData.label: sv_auto_cstrafe_sequence_length
uiData.helperText: The length of sequential counter-strafe attempts evaluated relative to the success threshold. Input automation detection considers the best sequence within the larger attempt window.

consoleData.description: The minimum number of successful counter-strafes within a best sequence that will trigger input automation detection. The number of successes that trigger input automation detection is interpolated between the success threshold and a 'perfect' sequence (all counter-strafes in a sequence are successes), depending on the player's percentage of overlapping counter-strafe attempts.

uiData.label: sv_auto_cstrafe_success_threshold
uiData.helperText: The minimum number of successful counter-strafes within a best sequence that will trigger input automation detection. The number of successes that trigger input automation detection is interpolated between the success threshold and a 'perfect' sequence (all counter-strafes in a sequence are successes), depending on the player's percentage of overlapping counter-strafe attempts.

consoleData.description: The percentage of overlapping attempts in the attempt window below which input automation detection is triggered when all counter-strafes in a sequence are successes.

uiData.label: sv_auto_cstrafe_upper_overlap_pct_threshold
uiData.helperText: The percentage of overlapping attempts in the attempt window below which input automation detection is triggered when all counter-strafes in a sequence are successes.
